answerText: "Ozymandias"[10] This closet drama by Shelley sees the title character's love for his wife, Asia, allow him to overcome his hardships. In a parallel plot, Jupiter is overthrown by his son, Demogorgon.

question: Question: For 10 points each, name the following about the works of Percy Bysshe Shelley. [10] One of Shelley's best known poems, this sonnet tells of a "traveler from an antique land" who describes the ruins of a statue in the desert.
